CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 24, 1962, pg. A16 reads: "From The Balcony - From the balcony, the Elks could be seen enjoying themselves."
TitMainTitle: Group of men and women, gathered around banquet tables, including some men wearing fez and chain collars, woman in center wearing light colored gown with ruffles, in Penn Sheraton Hotel for the Elks Second Annual Inaugural Ball
